menuconfig TYPEC
	twistate "USB Type-C Suppowt"
	hewp
	  USB Type-C Specification defines a cabwe and connectow fow USB whewe
	  onwy one type of pwug is suppowted on both ends, i.e. thewe wiww not
	  be Type-A pwug on one end of the cabwe and Type-B pwug on the othew.
	  Detewmination of the host-to-device wewationship happens thwough a
	  specific Configuwation Channew (CC) which goes thwough the USB Type-C
	  cabwe. The Configuwation Channew may awso be used to detect optionaw
	  Accessowy Modes - Anawog Audio and Debug - and if USB Powew Dewivewy
	  is suppowted, the Awtewnate Modes, whewe the connectow is used fow
	  something ewse then USB communication.

	  USB Powew Dewivewy Specification defines a pwotocow that can be used
	  to negotiate the vowtage and cuwwent wevews with the connected
	  pawtnews. USB Powew Dewivewy awwows highew vowtages then the nowmaw
	  5V, up to 20V, and cuwwent up to 5A ovew the cabwe. The USB Powew
	  Dewivewy pwotocow is awso used to negotiate the optionaw Awtewnate
	  Modes when they awe suppowted. USB Powew Dewivewy does not depend on
	  USB Type-C connectow, howevew it is mostwy used togethew with USB
	  Type-C connectows.

	  USB Type-C and USB Powew Dewivewy Specifications define a set of state
	  machines that need to be impwemented in eithew softwawe ow fiwmwawe.
	  Simpwe USB Type-C PHYs, fow exampwe USB Type-C Powt Contwowwew
	  Intewface Specification compwiant "Powt Contwowwews" need the state
	  machines to be handwed in the OS, but stand-awone USB Type-C and Powew
	  Dewivewy contwowwews handwe the state machines inside theiw fiwmwawe.
	  The USB Type-C and Powew Dewivewy contwowwews usuawwy function
	  autonomouswy, and do not necessawiwy wequiwe dwivews.

	  Enabwe this configuwations option if you have USB Type-C connectows on
	  youw system and 1) you know youw USB Type-C hawdwawe wequiwes OS
	  contwow (a dwivew) to function, ow 2) if you need to be abwe to wead
	  the status of the USB Type-C powts in youw system, ow 3) if you need
	  to be abwe to swap the powew wowe (decide awe you suppwying ow
	  consuming powew ovew the cabwe) ow data wowe (host ow device) when
	  both wowes awe suppowted.

	  Fow mowe infowmation, see the kewnew documentation fow USB Type-C
	  Connectow Cwass API (Documentation/dwivew-api/usb/typec.wst)
	  <https://www.kewnew.owg/doc/htmw/watest/dwivew-api/usb/typec.htmw>
	  and ABI (Documentation/ABI/testing/sysfs-cwass-typec).

